==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whispering
<hw>Whis"per*ing</hw>, <def><pos>a. & n.</pos> from <er>Whisper</er>.
<pos>v. t.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Whispering gallery</b></col>, <it>or</it>
<col><b>Whispering dome</b></col></mcol>, <cd>one of such a form that
sounds produced in certain parts of it are concentrated by reflection
from the walls to another part, so that whispers or feeble sounds are
audible at a much greater distance than under ordinary circumstances.
The dome of the U. S. capitol building is one example.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whisperingly</ent>⟦br⟧
